            <tr><td colspan="2" class="mhback" align="right"><span class="fs8"><a class="mh" href="/db/classes.html?class=12"><img src="/shared/root_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Up" width="17" height="11" /> Thread Index</a> |  <a class="mh" href="/db/classes.html?class=12;post=1"><img src="/shared/new_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="New" width="17" height="11" /> New Subject</a> | <a class="mh" href="/db/classes.html?class=12;mid=10718479612375;post=1"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply" width="17" height="11" /> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr> <tr><td colspan="2"><table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2"><a name="10718479612375"></a><span class="msgSubject">Magician's, are not so magical after all.</span><br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Magician's, are not so magical after all.";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Dec 19th  2003 at 11:31am EDT<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=12;mid=10718479612375;post=1;replyto=10718479612375"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    </span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=272332"><span class="">stonehouse</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br />3 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=12;mid=10718479612375;page=;howmany=50#10718479612375"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>The problem I have playing a mage is that, overall they offer very little to a group or a raid. About the only thing most 60+ level raids will require from a mage is CoH! Face it, as mages go we're not setup for high level raiding. Every supposed upgrade magicians have had from the expansions, is really stuff that's been added as an after though. These are ablilities that we should of had from the start. The spells that are bearly worth having are all 60th or higher, and tend to be far too specialized to be used often. (These spells need to have the level requirements lowered, IMO) <br /> <br />As far as the pets go, consider that any unfocused pet will be about 3 to 4 levels lower then the mage summoning it. (Hence it being the agro magnet from hell) Worst of all, we just don't have &quot;a&quot; pet, we have 4 different types. Each with their own abilities depending on the element they are summoned from, which sounds great in theory, but hasn't worked out very well in practice. Lets take the Fire pet for instance... It's modeled after the wizard, and can cast and buff as one. This would be very useful if it weren't for two things. The pet goes OOM after buffing / first 2 nukes, and jumps into melee agroing and dying rather quickly because it has nothing for hit points or AC. Makes me wonder what Verant / Sony was smoking to think this pet model would be a great idea? <br /> <br />Adding insult to injury, our epic just about blows! First off we have the hardest Epic in the game bar none. Second, most guilds will not assist a magician with their epic's, as it offers nothing to improve the overall strength of the guild. Sure the pet is great, as long as your fighting mobs &lt; 60th level, and you don't have any of the post 60th level pets. Beyond that it's ends up being the &quot;Back-up pet&quot;, as most mages I know won't use them without a focus item. <br /> <br />Lets not even start me on pet weapons...! <br /> <br />The really sad thing is, I have to 2'Box my 65th mage with a 56th cleric, to keep up with a beastlord of the same level! (Not considering AA's and gear) <br /> <br />Overall, I believe mages need a major overhaul to be a worthwhile class with in EQ. Other wise, it's just a class to play as an Alt, not as a Main. <br /> <br />-Stoner <br /></p>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >26 replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
