<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>One of the big mage benefits on a raid needs to be stressed. CoH! Many raids can be cut to half the normal time, if a mage Calls the other members of the raid through the zone, rather than having to fight past the mobs. <br /> <br />Throw in the fact that ALL pet classes will want a pet kit, and ALL casters want a mod rod. For certain circumstances, or for underequipped apps/members, the mage summoned focus items can also make or break a raid. <br /> <br />So, before the raid even starts, the mage is crucial. THEN on top of that, once the raid is under way, the mage is good dps, and has a pet that's capable of off tanking a minor add, if needed, or is additional dps. <br /> <br />Mage epic isn't worthless. I guess you've never seen an epic mage chain cast pets (mana free) against an AOE or high DS mob, while saving ALL their mana for nukes. Besides, there are really only a couple epics that ARE really decent these days.Play a paladin for a while, then see if you really think the mage epic is bad. <br /> <br />OH, btw: my guild was in Plane of Sky last night, working on mage epics. As a bonus, we got something like 6 drops for ranger epics (only one ranger needed, other 5 held for guild MQ). If your guild doesn't help, perhaps either 1) you have not yet earned the help, or 2) your guild isn't so hot. <br /> <br />Oh, one last thing. Why talk about UNFOCUSED mage pets? Since the Diamond Prism of Companionship  <br />( <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23480" title="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23480" target="akztarg">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23480</a> ) is available to ANY mage, even without a guild, any 60+ mage who doesn't have this, has no right to complain about the level of his pets. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Tue Jul  6 11:44:50 2004 by xaanru</span></i></p>
