<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>While I agree with some of what your saying, I do not agree with it all. <br />Lets take your typical MPG group as an example. 1 warrior, 1 chanter, 1 pally, 1 shaman, 1 bard, + 1 whatever class, in this case mage. At absolute best, the pally and warrior combined equal the DPS of a mage only EP geared. If that mage is is time, GoD, or anguish geared, as well as those two... the mage still out DPS's them. AA's make agro a very small problem and if the warrior bothered with his 1.5 like he should have by the time he is in MPG... it even adds more to the effect. Bottom line is, except for short bursts, a mage is probably the greatest DPS class there is bar noe. I might give wizzies the benifit of the doubt being I never seen a GoD or anguish geared wizzy... but I do not know as I never seen one. <br /> <br />Now saying that, yes, mages are hard to play and get their epic (1.0 is a real PITA, 1.5 is cake in comparison). And unless they spend their AA's in the right places, a mage is not too group useful and a raid nightmare. The problem is with their deceptive AA's. Being a mage with AA's is the most potent solo class there is, most mages spend those AA's to solo... groups / raids like you say have little use for for them as they are a liability instead of a asset. They become more of a asset trying to become a great mage buying/obtaining solo gear instead of concentrating on benificial group/raid AA's because they typically get shun down from those groups by spending AA's in the wrong places just so they can become better solo'er's. <br /> <br />But lets face it, if a mage is GoD geared (not time, everyone farms that zone with little skill), that mage knows how to play the toon. Then he/she is a great raid/group asset and are repeatedly called as even at lower level's, they can out DPS a warrior with 950+ AA's at level 66 and minimal AA's. DPS is not the name of the group tho, it is the ability to play the toon... most just concentrate on the worthless bazaar gear and learn how to play the toon as they want level's thinking level's/named OoW twink gear is as good as GoD, most just try to level instead of thinking upon proper character advancement. Therein lies the problem, not the class ability, but the attitude of the player playing a mage. <br /> <br />It is not a class specific issue either. Take druid for example. They are a great group asset, but most end up soloing because they dont know how to advance, so they go for solo abilities... maybe it has something to do with the bazaar a PP with companies like IGE buying/selling PP. Rather instead of group/raiod progressin... that person want to solo the best in hopes of making money off the game. Being they go for solo abilities... they give the class a bad group/raid liability because of greed.... I dont know... come up with your own idea's. But a proper mage that knows what he is doing is a great group/raid asset.</p>
