<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>You have a point Candayen, however I'll go you one further. It's not the AA, or even the gear that makes the mage. But almost pure play style. It comes down to what you as an individual are capable of. Mages can CC, track, pull, tank and heal... all at once! Now myself, I'm only OoW geared. No anguish or even time as (silly me) I went with a family guild over a raid guild. Only 200ish AA. Point being, in spite of that, I have a pretty damn healthy relationship with the top guilds on the server. Why? Because I have tried my damnedest to learn every trick a mage can do. See, there's the obvious stuff; AA, clickies, etc.. But there's a whole underground store of mage knowledge. Tricks that never make the forums or the web pages. Stuff that isn't (and shouldn't be) common knowledge. <br /> <br />Now that said, the average mage is a LOT better off nowadays then back in PoP. Sony actually listened to a lot of the complaints and addressed them, to a serious degree. Our 66+ pets, for lack of a better phrase, kick serious arse. (scept fire, but that's been the red-headed stepchild since the mid 50's) We've crit nukes that can break 8k with the proper AA. I frequently get the wizzies pissed at me for out critting them. In edition to that, there's the soloing thing. Not so much for exp these days, but with the new heal a lot of Named become soloable for fun and serious profit. If you know where to look. All in all, the mage class is <i>finally</i> getting pretty darn close to balance. At this point, even without the gear and the AA you can still do some stuff that'll make the peanut gallery's jaw's drop. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />Arch Magus Faelawen Starfyre, the Legendary Mad Mage of Povar, Arch Nemesis of the Evil Squirrel Empire. (AMFSTLMMOPANOTESE for short) Proud officer of RasCals.</p>
