<p>Good suggestion. Time consuming quests create a sense of accomplishment. I would rather collect 10 000 rat ears to hand in than sit for 12 hours waiting for a spawn to finally drop something that should not have been a rare drop since LDON came out. <br /> <br />Use of the task system for Epic 1.0 (at least) and other old quests makes sense. Personally, I would like to see an alternate path put in so you can do your epic traditionally or a more solo based-appropriate-to-the-level (say 50? for epic 1.0) route. Also, allow the two ways to interact so you could mix and match. <br /> <br />Give the people with existing epics a special augment or something (i.e., &quot;veteran's epic stone of power&quot;) to recognize the effort put in prior to such a... simplification. If it makes the game more playable = fun, then that is good. <br /> <br />*this post was in repsonse to a thread above discussing walk thrus of the epic 1.0 using the task menu set up. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Fri Sep 30 07:24:18 2005 by tworok</span></i></p>
