<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=12;mid=10718479612375;page=;howmany=50#10718479612375"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p> A lot has changed since this thread was begun in 2003, and most of it for the better. <br /> <br /> As a solo class, the Mage is not the most potent. The combinations afforded to Necros give them, IMHO, a slight edge here. But the edge is slight!. We can now solo a lot of areas and make fair XP and/or good Plat if we want. (Learning to chaincast is a great skill) <br /> <br /> In the higher levels, I find myself pretty popular for grouping. Especially with knowledgable players. With the high grade DS for our melee friends and Mod Rods for the casters we add a lot to the base of the group. Figure in the DPS from the pets and nukes that regularly run in the 7K range and we add tons. CoH, lev and invis are helpful, but the ability to use your pet as the off tank in many areas (chain casting again) provides security in case things go bad. Folks that know the game love to have a Mage around! <br /> <br /> When it comes to Raids, things change for everyone. CoH may not seem like a big deal to some, but try getting extra toons to your raids in KT by running them there. In many of the higher level areas, CoH can save an unbelievable amount of time. On top of that, set up a Pyrilen Skin rotation for the MA along the lines of the heal rotation. When the mobs(that hit fast even when slowed) are taking an additional 450+pts from the DS every time they land a hit, it adds up fast. We still throw our nukeage and pets for damage too. Take a look at the DPS parse from raids that have a few Mages there. It's something special. <br /> <br /> All in all, Mages have been doing pretty well through the expansions. If you want to land bigger nukes, roll a Wizzy. If you want to be the 'Best&quot; soloer, try a necro. But if you want a good all-around class that is fun to play in most situations and has something good to add to all of them, then a Mage is a good choice! <br /> <br /> Of course, this only applies to Gnomes. =)</p>
