<p>&quot;X class is not necessary on raids&quot; <br /> <br />This phrase has been used millions of times. <br /> <br />What, exactly, is necessary on raids then? <br /> <br />I assumed it was DPS, Crowd Control, Healing and Tanking.  Not in any particular order. (For all intents and purposes, a Haste buff is DPS and a Cleric shield buff is tanking and so forth) <br /> <br />Every class in Everquest can provide at least one of these, some classes provide more than one. <br /> <br />Your Magician should provide DPS at minimum.  An air pet, lv 66 and above, can off-tank.  It is a sight to see. <br /> <br /></p>
